just DONT take any courses with him. take Iris's class for MGEB06 they have 2 hours for the midterm for the same number of questions, same material and kinda the same questions but Parkinson's midterms are 1.5

rComments: His classes are absolutely miserable. I had him for both MGEA02 and MGEB06 and I have done terribly in both classes. His exam questions are an appetizer for hell. If you can avoid him, then avoid him. If not, then I wish you the best and RIP. His textbooks are useless and he teaches so ambiguously. He needs a life changing experience to smarten up.

I regret this class so much. He's horrible at explaining things and once he starts talking, you can feel the energy being sucked out of the room. You can try getting by off the documents available online, but that's also difficult. My advice, wait for another prof to be available in another semester.

His exams are straight up the most brutal exams I ever wrote. Like, you either know it or you dont, however, I never experienced this as harshly as with this professor. 50% of exams questions were vaguely worded. Textbook is absolutely useless. If you are not economics or management major dont even come ANYWHERE close to his class.
teacherRatingTags: ['Test heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: He teaches very well, but his assignments and exams are very hard! Textbooks are always useless in his courses. He's always willing to help his students and is always quick with responding to emails.  He normally bell curves the exam marks when the class does bad. Attending class and taking good notes is crucial to do well in this course.

He's a wonderful prof, his teaches the course very well in the lectures. He cares about you too, so don't be afraid to ask questions. The textbook is useless, can't believe i wasted $150 on that. I had an 87 before the final, and have would have gotten a 4.0 if i studied more. After only 1 day of studying for the final my final mark was a B+
Worst prof ever. His exams are brutal literally you can study weeks before and can still fail. Although his lectures notes are decent, he cannot teach.

Worst prof ever. His lectures are boring and he keeps on telling HORRIBLE jokes, thinking people would laugh. All his classes are recorded, so you DONT have to go to any of the lectures yourself. Believe me, save yourself the trouble and DO NOT TAKE IT WITH HIM
I love him. He's super out there, and it's just adorable. His examples drag on a bit, but he makes things clear.

Good teacher, but actively contributes to a toxic atmosphere by gossiping. Stay on his good side, and if you are not drop the course. Will sometimes share juicy details about other professors, but don't be fooled will also share juicy details about you with other professors too.

I found pakinson to be a really good professor, he was clear when teaching he gave really good examples and he was funny at the same time! He really knew what he was talking about and his lectures, albeit long as they were 3hrs, weren't hard to follow. You do have to know your material for his tests! read the book and know your theories inside out!

rComments: Funny prof who explains each topic pretty well and provides examples. However, his exams are fairly difficult

His explanations are amazing . Both clear and concise. He knows how to suppose them with examples. He is very friendly and approachable. Only downside are his midterms and final exams. They are insanely hard. Its either you understand it or you don't.  Best way to prepare for them is by completing recommended readings and doing practice exercises.
His lecture notes are amazing! He writes them all on the board so if you skip class you'll miss the note because it is not posted on blackboard. He only does powerpoints sometimes
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Very good at explaining all the concepts! I felt like I learned something about economics. However his exams are tricky. BUT his classes usually have very low work loads! Great if you just want some econ credits while learning some interesting stuff.
his notes are unorganized. Seldom explain the important concepts and instead spending most of the time telling dry jokes.

You have to go to class to do well. He is a bit boring but explains concepts well - if you pay attention (a bit hard to do). Exams are difficult and not much previous material to study from. Expect a bell for the final and try and take the course with another prof. Experience? 6/10.

Boring class, all self studying, still got A. Notes are messy. Jokes are dry... He spends lots of time telling dry jokes. Midterm is easy, like the old exams, final is unbelievabllly hard, I guess he curved 10 marks at least.... I don't know what the final exam is asking for but surprisingly stii got an A...
He is a great professor for economics. He makes everything in point form and easy to understand. Final exam is hard, have to study hard for the old exams.

Attending lectures is a must. I in general do not like economics, but I find Parkinson clear, knowledgeable, and fair. I actually barely passed the midterm and did extremely well on the exam so that became my final mark, replacing the midterm! Past exams are definitely helpful. Good luck!

Great professor, very clear! Attend your lectures; it's boring to listen to him online. He says the main facts over and over again, to make sure it's drilled in your head. Do the past finals; it'll save your butt! Overall, great professor.

A very nice, knowledgeable and crystal clear professor (the type clearly been teaching for decades). HOWEVER, he gives some of the toughest exams I've ever seen. Class average is usually 60. The exams are also extremely long (barely able to finish). Very messy notes (chicken scrawl on blackboard) too, and did NOT provide sample exams this year.

I like him as a prof.... until I walked into the final exam for summer 2012 ECMB06 class. Good thing I had a 90+ before the final to cushion the blow. Note to future students: do REALLY well on midterm, because his final exam in my experience is very tricky.
Make sure you understand the concepts before you walk in to his exams.  Class is a must, cuz he tests extensively on the material from class notes.  Nice guy, but exams can be tricky.
Monotone and boring, the material is also dry. Final was quite hard, he puts a lot of random stuff on it that we don't touch on in class. Would not recommend.
Messy notes, hard to organize or prepare for the exam. Have no clue during the class. However, he is nice though.

Had him for ecmb06 as well and he is such an amazing professor! Teaches clearly and give many examples to help you understand the material better. He also gives you past assignments/exams to help you prepare for the final!. Very good professor, I wish I could have him for every econ course I need!

ECMB06; Honestly he is an amazing professor. His lectures are very boring but if you do all the required work for the course you will do well and make friends with the TAs! As he says in class hes not out to trick his students he is a fair professor and if you study you're guaranteed an 80 at least! Even go to his office hours HE IS VERY NICE!

He is okay prof but his lecture notes are really messed up and  doesnt match up with what he teaches in the class.However his TA was really good.. One advise-please see his TA and ask him what he prefers...book or lecture notes...For most of the time its TA who marks the exam..
I don't know if its him or the course material. It was hard to follow him in class.I don't suggest anyone to take ECMB06 with him.

His notes were really messy and his lectures were awful. Whatever "double tilde" meant... it sure wasn't in the book. His exams were really tough, but I did well. My recommendation? STUDY THE BOOK (NOT his notes). I agree that he can get quite cocky.
A very god professor.

Decent prof. Very cocky and as a result can be condescending when you ask him questions... His lectures are pure theory while his exams are mostly math based. TIP: He will always put ONE stupid/easy question on the exam, but everybody usually over-thinks the question and gets it wrong.
The worse prof i have ever met. he is such a rude person...never go see him in person...if you have questions ask him in class

I think he's quite helpful. and I love his midterm policies. I had several class with him, and if you score higher in the Final u can always replace the midters. and you can miss ur midterm for whatever reason xD...
NOTES SUCKED!!! Hardly posted notes, improvised during class! A big dissappointment = 2 thumbs down !
out of all the courses he teaches, he teaches this course the best. Just need his lecture notes and you will do well.  very clear with his concepts and explains thoroughly. Very knowledgable
The best prof I've met in UTSC. He explains concepts extremely clearly. His course is a must take.
He is a great prof.  I really enjoyed his teaching style and his humor is great.  His tests are challenging but if you look at previous tests you should become accustomed with his style.
